metadata.description:
Sometimes when you're working on your Creative Coding project, you make a change to the code and it breaks. But maybe that's a good thing. This project was created as a fun expression of what can happen if you allow yourself to go down the rabbit hole, and further break your code until you come up with a new idea.

metadata.name: Pixel Blobs II #406
metadata.description:
This is a "zero player game" partially inspired by Conway's Game of Life. Between 4-10 pixel blobs are places on a screen and autonomously grow based on a deterministic set of rules. The game ends when all of the available cells are occupied by a blob. Some blobs prefer to slowly expand evenly in every direction. Other blobs prefer to aggressively push all of their energy into a single direction gobbling up as much territory as possible.

There is no single "victory condition". Maybe you care about the conquest of a single blob controlling as much space or energy as possible. Or maybe you prefer blobs to collaborate to create beautiful chaotic patterns.

Controls:
- 's' Saves a PNG of the current screen.
- 'i' Restarts the game in "infinite mode". 10 seconds after each game ends, the rules are shuffled and the game resets.

metadata.name: The Color of Spring #28
metadata.description:
“Color of Spring” : Seasons of Siskiyou Series
By Ed Cavett
March 2022

Description of Seasons of Siskiyou Series
Surrounding my home, covering more than one million acres, is the Rogue River - Siskiyou National Forest which takes up three southern Oregon counties and one northern California county.  It’s a magical place that fills the imagination and lifts the spirit; a place that inspires with its uniqueness, its legends, and its larger-than-life vistas.

Each season in the Siskiyou mountains is a unique experience unto itself.  So, with an attention to the feelings this place evokes at any given time of the year, I designed four generative tokens to create an impression of the emotion–the calming quietness; the peaceful solitude; the overwhelming contrasts and variety of forms, shapes and textures; the magic and playful mystery; the welcomingness and foreboding.  These four works feature clever and inventive creative coding techniques in a rich, graphic style to craft a stunning impression of the Seasons of Siskiyou.


Token 1 of 4 - THE COLOR OF SPRING (1990 x 1080) p5js Generative Token.

The Color of Spring captures the playfulness and joy of the season of birth; the renewal and hopefulness of a bounty that follows warmth and light.  The weight of winter and the burdens of darkness melt away with the length of the day.  The monotones of a gray-chromatic winter bristle with bursts of bright colors in an ocean of budding green.  Magic brings forth the harbingers of fruit and the fleeting, nostalgic notes of newness and surprise.  In such a place, in such a time, we are transported back to when this was the world, and all there was in it.  With a child-mind, we are suspended in that instant while we relive all the moments like it.  And, before we have time to grow tired of it, it disappears into the brilliant light of summer.       

Output and Coding Features of “The Color of Spring”:

This generative token features a stand of aspen that borders a field of wildflowers in a sea of lush, green grass.  Animated pixies tend to the flowers as they wave their wands while fluttering about the field.  Fuzzy orbs of light dance around each pixie with some that glide capricious throughout the scene.

Press UP ARROW to toggle the scene on/off leaving only the pixies and glowing orbs.  Press RIGHT ARROW to toggle Pause and Play.  Press LEFT ARROW to toggle Add and Remove pixies.  The static scene has a blurry particle effect added in.  Press DOWN ARROW to save the current frame as a png image file.  The file will be downloaded to a local folder. 


Collectors can choose to pause the animation and freeze the scene on a static image.  If collectors so desire, they may remove the pixies from the scene and appreciate the simple beauty without distraction.  Capture an image as a downloadable image file by pressing the Down Arrow.

The aspens are generated using flow-field stochastic conditions for an organic structure, and with a random expression of knots as the object is formed.

The grass and flower pedals are generated using recursions that incorporate noise-stochastic conditions.

The pixies are generated with primitive geometries using a “marionette” style structure.  The animation is achieved through noise-stochastic conditions that rotate segments, such as the arms, legs and feet.

Each iteration varies the order and appearance of the graphic elements; the number of pixies and the number of flowers.   

Token Published April 16, 2022 on FXHASH set at 75 Editions.
Written and designed by Ed Cavett using the p5js library.
Token 1 of 4 from the series “The Seasons of Siskiyou.”

metadata.name: Spira #262
metadata.description:
Spira is a series of static pieces where lines are drawn symmetrically around a central pivot. Additionally it is possible for the piece to be "broken" in which case some of the symmetry is lost and instead a more complex asymmetrical piece is produced.

Features:
> Brokenness (A percentage to indicate how "broken" the piece is.)
> Rotation (Rotation of each iteration.)
> Palette (Colour palette.)
> Sectors (Number of sectors which form the rotational symmetry.)
> Iterations (Number of iterations - higher means more lines in each sector.)
> Spacing (The spacing between each iteration.)

Created by Lucas RiedlShah (@lucas_riedlshah)

metadata.name: Ripple / Cymatic #236
metadata.description:
Mathematical animations inspired by cymatics.  

Symmetric waves ripple around a boundary, causing infinitely complex patterns that evolve forever but never repeat.

Variations are the frequencies and amplitudes of waves, the boundary shape, and the velocity of phase shifts.

Some are contained, others escape to infinity.

metadata.description:
My previous Token "Patched" had an issue where different viewport sizes rendered slightly different outputs. At the time I was not able to correct this but now I am!
Patched and Mended has different palettes from the original, including a monochrome version, and doesn't have a resizing issue.

metadata.name: Isomeric doppelgangers #47
metadata.description:
'Isomeric doppelgangers' 

Spatial isomerism, is a form of isomerism in which molecules have the same molecular formula and sequence of bonded atoms (constitution), but differ in the three-dimensional orientations of their atoms in space.

This artworks flips several boxes on the X or Y axis, resulting in two gemelar images, each with the same palette but a different color mix. The perception of diverse scenes is based only on these modifications.

The collection is limited to 100 works of art.

-----

Press 's' to save the current canvas view.

-----

Features:

Palette: coral, gray, retro, vrolik3, origami, sooph, jfa, bell
Zoom: low, medium, high, random
Orientation: portrait, vertical
Fill: true, false


-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Murals #221
metadata.description:
'Murals' is a collection of 256 abstract compositions born out of an intense period diving deeply into street art, pointillism and the inner workings of neural networks.

The work explores projection, refraction and abstraction of points as they ripple through multi-dimensional space-time. Points refract through multi-dimensional space to become shapes, which then become coordinate systems for the projections of new points that create a sense of form, texture, lighting, and material properties. 

The work is also a celebration of imperfections and how a combination of many tiny – almost individually imperceptibly small – imperfect details can shape our perceptions of form, materiality, mood. This is explored within this work through subtle uses of sprays, flecks, scuffs, cuts, grain, targets (projections of projections), construction lines, base projections, occasional glitches that cause curvature, bounced light, shadows, and more.

Features:

15 colour palettes: 
Scream, Night Bus, Double Backflip, Jaws, Sunday, Atom, Space, Tipex, 
Graphite, Leaf, Earth, Bubble Gum, Citrus, Jellyfish, Damp Concrete.

4 times of day (that create subtle changes in light colour):
Daylight, Winter Morning, Midnight, Sunset

2 Border types: 
Normal, Thin

Various features that subtly impact appearance surface textures and shard forms:
Metallic, Engrave, Number of Shards, Scuff Marks, Symmetry. 

Controls:
- Press [ S ] to save the work at its current image size as a PNG.
- Press [ 1 ] to set the image size to 1440 x 1944 pixels (default size)
- Press [ 2 ] to set the image size to 2880 x 3888 pixels
- Press [ 3 ] to set the image size to 4320 x 5832 pixels

- Press [ F ] to toggle freeform mode to create custom image sizes and aspect ratios
- Press [ R ] to reload the image (for use in freeform mode)

This work has been tested on Chrome and Safari on Mac OS, and also using an Android smartphone. Please make sure that it works on your device before minting. Based on testing (in May 2022), each work should take about 5-10 seconds to fully load on a laptop or desktop machine, and 15-20 seconds on a mobile device. The loading process is animated so you can watch the construction the static artwork during this time. 

This artwork is created with p5.js 

@nbswwit, 2022
